          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measuring the yield of 0.511 mev gamma-quanta",
                " emitted following annihilation of positrons from the",
                " induced 9.97 min positron activity of N-13."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three samples, each weighing 24.9 g, were in the form",
                " of  discs  of  diameter 31.85 mm and thickness 18.66",
                " mm.   They   were   formed   under   pressure   from",
                " ammonium-sulfate powder ((N(H-4)-2)S(o-4)) which was",
                " enriched to 98% in N-15."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Annihilation radiation of positrons from the",
                " activity of N-13."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD",
                "PLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The yield at a given energy is determined",
                " by the number of 0.511 MeV gamma  rays  detected  at",
                " that  energy.  Yield points were measured at 200 keV",
                " intervals from 21  to  28  MeV.  A  total  of  three",
                " separate  measurements  was  made  over  this  whole",
                " range. These three runs were averaged. this averaged",
                " curve  was  then  analyzed  using  the  variable bin",
                " Penfold-Leiss method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Root-mean-squared errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic errors are only estimated to be",
                "about 10%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross section for  the  N-15(g,2n)  reaction  has",
                " been  studied  from 20 to 28 MeV.  The cross section",
                " remains near zero for 3 MeV  above  threshold,  then",
                " rises sharply at about 24 MeV, to a maximum value of",
                " 1.7 mb.  The shape is  explained  in  terms  of  the",
                " density  of  states  with  isospin T> in N-14 at the",
                " relevant excitation energy.  It must be  noted  that",
                " the  present  measurement  determines only the cross",
                " section for transitions leading to the ground  state",
                " of final nucleus N-13, i.e. the cross section of the",
                " reaction N-15(g,nn-0)N-13-g.  All excited states  of",
                " N-13   (the  first  is  at  2.365  MeV)  are  proton",
                " unstable."
              ]
            }
          ],
